To visually select travel destinations on a map, you can use an interactive map with markers or pins. Here’s a breakdown of how you can implement this interactive element:

1. **Map Integration**: Use a mapping library or API such as Google Maps, Mapbox, Leaflet, or OpenLayers. These libraries provide comprehensive functionality for embedding and interacting with a map on your website.

2. **Markers/Icons**: Add markers or icons to corresponding locations on the map. Each marker can represent a travel destination. You can customize the appearance to match your brand or site’s style.

3. **Popup Information**: When a user clicks on a marker, a popup or tooltip can appear to display information about the travel destination such as the name, description, photos, or a link to more detailed information.

4. **Interactivity**: Implement interactivity such as zooming, panning, and selecting different layers of information based on categories like hotels, attractions, or restaurants.

Here is an example using Google Maps API:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>Travel Destination Map</title>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<style>
    #map {
        height: 400px;  /* Adjust height as needed */
        width: 100%;
    }
</style>
<script src="https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/js?key=YOUR_API_KEY"></script>
<script>
    function initMap() {
        // Create a new map
        var map = new google.maps.Map(document.getElementById('map'), {
            center: {lat: -34.397, lng: 150.644},
            zoom: 6
        });

        // Define some destinations
        var destinations = [
            {name: 'Sydney', lat: -33.8688, lng: 151.2093},
            {name: 'Melbourne', lat: -37.8136, lng: 144.9631},
            {name: 'Brisbane', lat: -27.4698, lng: 153.0251}
        ];

        // Add markers to the map
        destinations.forEach(function(dest) {
            var marker = new google.maps.Marker({
                position: {lat: dest.lat, lng: dest.lng},
                map: map,
                title: dest.name
            });

            // Add an info window/click event
            marker.addListener('click', function() {
                var infoWindow = new google.maps.InfoWindow({
                    content: '<h1>' + dest.name + '</h1>'
                });
                infoWindow.open(map, marker);
            });
        });
    }
</script>
</head>
<body onload="initMap()">
    <div id="map"></div>
</body>
</html>
```

In this example:
- A Google Map is initialized with an initial center and zoom level.
- Custom destinations are defined with their locations.
- Markers are created for each destination and added to the map.
- Each marker opens an info window with basic destination details when clicked.

